children.subject:
I took EECS 127 last semester and it was pretty much all math to begin with. It really helped taking Math 110 at the same time. I wouldn't say it's too difficult but I didn't do that well in 16A/B so I had a pretty rough start in both classes.

Last semester they spent about 2.5 weeks reviewing previous material (Linear algebra, Symmetric Matrices, SVD, Low Rank Approximation, Vector Calc), so it was a good opportunity to get up to speed.

Idk how Prof. Anantharam will pace it this year, but the work last semester should be reasonable if you did well in 16A/B.

history.content:
So I will be taking 127 this fall, and I have heard prof. Venkat is more like a mathematician.

Is there anyone who have taken a class with the professor? How would you expect 127 taught by prof Venkat?

I took 16A/B and learnt quite well but I'm kind of concerned about the math portion he will be teaching.
